<p>Under tort law TRESPASS TO CHATTEL is an<strong> intentional act </strong>by the defendant causing unauthorized<strong> interferencce with or damage</strong> to the <strong>chattel of the plaintiff</strong>. The defendant is liable for actual damages measured as the lost rental value of the chattel, the rental costs for temporary replacement of the chattel, and the repair costs to repair the chattel, but usually not more than the actual cash value of the chattel.</p>
<p>Here ... because ...</p>
<p>Therefore the defendant may be liable for trespass to chattels.   </p>
